Any New Years parties scheduled?

In other news, I'm back from NH...and dead. Two weeks stress free has unfortunatly caught up with me. &gt;&lt;;
I am happy to be home though. I missed everyone over the holidays. ^__^

&gt;&lt; I'm going to post this now. PLEASE NO GIFTS FOR ME.
I'm broke due to having to pay ALL my expenses even rent over summer...which sucked up any savings I had, and so I barely have enough as is for next semester. So, please no gifts...because I can't get anyone anything. ;.; I won't be here over Christmas either. I leave right after finals to see my parentsfor 2 weeks, the fisrt of which I will have my wisdom teeth removed... &gt;&lt;&nbsp; 

Also, would anyone be willing to take careof my pets over Christmas? It would consist of making sure they have food/hay/water and scooping out thecats litterbox every so often. I'm willing to pay up front, so If Whit or anyone else needs a little extra holiday cash, let me know.

Told my brother I wanted to move out in april if any way possible. he told me it was stupid and I would be "throwing away money" I told him I didn't want to live with him and his new bride. He re-iterated it was stupid and I would be wasting money AND he couldn't afford this place himself. My answer "yeah, but you could afford a single bedroom appt too. If I'm thinking aboutdoing it certainly you COULD. HE reiterates it's a waste of money for him and me and says he can't support he and marlena both here. I tell him to move out, and that "You shouldn't get married if you can't support yourself and your spouse."&nbsp;

He's not speaking to me now.

Thing is though, he plans on moving out too most likely in June when he gets a new job. He doesn't know which STATE he will even be in. He SAYS he'll give me plenty of warning before he moves to wherever the hell. I told him I can wait till June, but I don't want to live with him and his new bride.&nbsp;
Is it so odd that if I can in any way afford it I want my own place. I don't care how small it is. I just want something my own. No more bitching about whos job what is, or who made what mess. Mine, all my messes, all my responsibility, and I could actually build my own credit. currently the appartment and all bills I'm helping to pay are under Davids name. It's my good credit history too...

Am I just being stubborn? Is it wrong to want my own place as long as I can still save for college?&nbsp;
